{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850968471,"sessionID":"ses_2870bf392ffeKZ8jL8UQ3Wxavm","part":{"id":"prt_d78f75444001Mk5eJ42QC0iOgo","messageID":"msg_d78f4d43c001gOmscbpNp6G0mN","sessionID":"ses_2870bf392ffeKZ8jL8UQ3Wxavm","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-e84a92a03cba4667b2fb8e91ff8f8f53","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\nModule: `pkg/router`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Router session management subsystem, providing session lifecycle management, sandbox routing, reverse proxy, JWT authentication, unified error handling, and middleware support for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter invocation requests.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: SessionManager Interface\n\n**GIVEN** the Router needs to manage sessions for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter  \n**WHEN** handling session-based routing requests  \n**THEN** SessionManager interface shall be properly defined with GetSandboxBySession method\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: SessionManager interface definition\nGIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\nWHEN reading the SessionManager interface\nTHEN it SHALL define GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n// Scenario 2: SessionManager implementation\nGIVEN pkg/router/session_manager.go\nWHEN reading the sessionManager struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain fields: storeClient Store, workloadMgrAddr string, httpClient *http.Client\n\n// Scenario 3: NewSessionManager constructor\nGIVEN pkg/router/session_manager.go\nWHEN calling NewSessionManager(storeClient Store)\nTHEN it SHALL read WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL from environment variable\nAND it SHALL return error if WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL is not set\nAND it SHALL configure HTTP client with 2 minute timeout and HTTP2 transport\n\n// Scenario 4: NewSessionManager environment requirement\nGIVEN WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable not set\nWHEN calling NewSessionManager(storeClient)\nTHEN it SHALL return error with message \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable is required\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: GetSandboxBySession Method\n\n**GIVEN** a session needs to be looked up or created  \n**WHEN** invoking GetSandboxBySession  \n**THEN** the method shall return existing sandbox or create a new one\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Existing session lookup\nGIVEN a sessionManager with Store containing session \"existing-session\"\nWHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"existing-session\", \"default\", \"test\", \"AgentRuntime\")\nTHEN it SHALL call storeClient.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"existing-session\")\nAND it SHALL return the existing SandboxInfo\n\n// Scenario 2: Empty sessionID creates new sandbox\nGIVEN a sessionManager with empty sessionID parameter\nWHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"\", \"default\", \"test-runtime\", \"AgentRuntime\")\nTHEN it SHALL call createSandbox to create new sandbox\nAND it SHALL NOT call storeClient.GetSandboxBySessionID\n\n// Scenario 3: Session not found error\nGIVEN a sessionManager with Store returning error for session \"nonexistent\"\nWHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"nonexistent\", \"default\", \"test\", \"AgentRuntime\")\nTHEN it SHALL return SessionNotFoundError with SessionID field set\n\n// Scenario 4: Namespace and name passed to createSandbox\nGIVEN a sessionManager creating new sandbox\nWHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"\", \"my-namespace\", \"my-runtime\", \"AgentRuntime\")\nTHEN createSandbox SHALL receive namespace=\"my-namespace\", name=\"my-runtime\", kind=\"AgentRuntime\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: CreateSandbox Method\n\n**GIVEN** a new sandbox needs to be created via WorkloadManager  \n**WHEN** calling createSandbox  \n**THEN** it shall send HTTP POST request to WorkloadManager and store the result\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: AgentRuntime endpoint selection\nGIVEN createSandbox with kind \"AgentRuntime\"\nWHEN building the HTTP request endpoint\nTHEN endpoint SHALL be workloadMgrAddr + \"/v1/agent-runtime\"\n\n// Scenario 2: CodeInterpreter endpoint selection\nGIVEN createSandbox with kind \"CodeInterpreter\"\nWHEN building the HTTP request endpoint\nTHEN endpoint SHALL be workloadMgrAddr + \"/v1/code-interpreter\"\n\n// Scenario 3: Unsupported kind error\nGIVEN createSandbox with kind \"UnsupportedKind\"\nWHEN executing the method\nTHEN it SHALL return error \"unsupported kind: UnsupportedKind\"\n\n// Scenario 4: Request body marshaling\nGIVEN createSandbox called\nWHEN building the HTTP request body\nTHEN body SHALL be JSON marshaled CreateSandboxRequest{Kind, Name, Namespace}\n\n// Scenario 5: Request validation\nGIVEN CreateSandboxRequest with invalid parameters\nWHEN calling Validate()\nTHEN it SHALL return error if Kind is not AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\nAND it SHALL return error if Namespace is empty\nAND it SHALL return error if Name is empty\n\n// Scenario 6: WorkloadManager HTTP error\nGIVEN WorkloadManager returning HTTP 500\nWHEN createSandbox processes response\nTHEN it SHALL return WorkloadManagerError with StatusCode 500\n\n// Scenario 7: Empty sessionId in response\nGIVEN WorkloadManager returning response with empty sessionId\nWHEN createSandbox processes response\nTHEN it SHALL return error \"empty sessionId in response\"\n\n// Scenario 8: Sandbox stored in Store\nGIVEN successful WorkloadManager response\nWHEN createSandbox processes response\nTHEN it SHALL call storeClient.StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\nAND sandbox SHALL have Kind, SandboxID, SandboxNamespace, SandboxName, Name, SessionID, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status, EntryPoints fields\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: Store Interface\n\n**GIVEN** the Router needs to persist and retrieve session data  \n**WHEN** managing session storage  \n**THEN** Store interface shall be properly defined\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Store interface definition\nGIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\nWHEN reading the Store interface\nTHEN it SHALL define GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\nAND it SHALL define StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\nAND it SHALL define UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n\n// Scenario 2: Store used by SessionManager\nGIVEN sessionManager struct\nWHEN reading the implementation\nTHEN storeClient field SHALL be of type Store\n\n// Scenario 3: Store used by Server\nGIVEN Server struct\nWHEN reading the implementation\nTHEN storeClient field SHALL be of type Store\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: Service Account Token\n\n**GIVEN** Router needs to authenticate with WorkloadManager  \n**WHEN** sending requests to WorkloadManager  \n**THEN** it shall use Kubernetes service account token\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: readServiceAccountToken function\nGIVEN pkg/router/session_manager.go\nWHEN reading readServiceAccountToken function\nTHEN it SHALL read from \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\nAND it SHALL return trimmed token string\n\n// Scenario 2: Token added to request header\nGIVEN createSandbox with valid service account token\nWHEN building HTTP request\nTHEN Authorization header SHALL be \"Bearer \" + saToken\n\n// Scenario 3: Token read error handled gracefully\nGIVEN service account token file not existing\nWHEN readServiceAccountToken returns error\nTHEN request SHALL proceed without Authorization header\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: Router Server Configuration\n\n**GIVEN** Router needs configurable HTTP server  \n**WHEN** setting up the server  \n**THEN** Config struct shall support all necessary options\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Config struct definition\nGIVEN pkg/router/config.go\nWHEN reading the Config struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain fields: Port string, EnableTLS bool, TLSCert string, TLSKey string, MaxConcurrentRequests int, Debug bool\n\n// Scenario 2: DefaultConfig function\nGIVEN pkg/router/config.go\nWHEN calling DefaultConfig()\nTHEN it SHALL return Config with Port \":8080\", EnableTLS false, MaxConcurrentRequests 1000, Debug false\n\n// Scenario 3: Server constructor with nil config\nGIVEN NewServer called with nil config\nWHEN constructing Server\nTHEN DefaultConfig SHALL be used\n\n// Scenario 4: MaxConcurrentRequests default\nGIVEN Config with MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0\nWHEN constructing Server\nTHEN MaxConcurrentRequests SHALL be set to 1000\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: Router Server Structure\n\n**GIVEN** Router needs HTTP server with Gin framework  \n**WHEN** constructing the Server  \n**THEN** Server struct shall contain all necessary components\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Server struct definition\nGIVEN pkg/router/server.go\nWHEN reading the Server struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain fields: config *Config, engine *gin.Engine, httpServer *http.Server, sessionManager SessionManager, storeClient Store, httpTransport *http.Transport, jwtManager *JWTManager, logger Logger\n\n// Scenario 2: Server constructor\nGIVEN pkg/router/server.go\nWHEN calling NewServer(config, sessionManager, storeClient, jwtManager, logger)\nTHEN it SHALL return *Server with all fields initialized\nAND gin.Engine SHALL be created with gin.New()\nAND http.Server SHALL have ReadTimeout 30s, IdleTimeout 90s\n\n// Scenario 3: Gin mode configuration\nGIVEN Config with Debug false\nWHEN constructing Server\nTHEN gin.SetMode SHALL be gin.ReleaseMode\n\n// Scenario 4: Gin mode with Debug true\nGIVEN Config with Debug true\nWHEN constructing Server\nTHEN gin.SetMode SHALL be gin.DebugMode\n\n// Scenario 5: registerRoutes called\nGIVEN NewServer constructing Server\nWHEN initialization completes\nTHEN registerRoutes SHALL be called\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-008: Router Route Registration\n\n**GIVEN** Router needs RESTful API endpoints  \n**WHEN** registering routes  \n**THEN** all endpoints shall be properly registered with middleware\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Health endpoints registered\nGIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\nWHEN reading route registration\nTHEN /health/live endpoint SHALL be registered with GET method\nAND /health/ready endpoint SHALL be registered with GET method\n\n// Scenario 2: AgentRuntime invocation endpoints\nGIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\nWHEN reading route registration\nTHEN /v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path SHALL be registered with GET and POST methods\n\n// Scenario 3: CodeInterpreter invocation endpoints\nGIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\nWHEN reading route registration\nTHEN /v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path SHALL be registered with GET and POST methods\n\n// Scenario 4: Middleware applied to v1 group\nGIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\nWHEN reading v1 route group\nTHEN concurrencyLimitMiddleware SHALL be applied\nAND loggingMiddleware SHALL be applied if logger is not nil\nAND recoveryMiddleware SHALL be applied if logger is not nil\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-009: Health Endpoints\n\n**GIVEN** Kubernetes needs liveness and readiness probes  \n**WHEN** implementing health endpoints  \n**THEN** proper health responses shall be returned\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: handleHealthLive endpoint\nGIVEN GET request to /health/live\nWHEN handler executes\nTHEN response SHALL be HTTP 200 with JSON {\"status\": \"alive\"}\n\n// Scenario 2: handleHealthReady with SessionManager\nGIVEN GET request to /health/ready with valid SessionManager\nWHEN handler executes\nTHEN response SHALL be HTTP 200 with JSON {\"status\": \"ready\"}\n\n// Scenario 3: handleHealthReady without SessionManager\nGIVEN GET request to /health/ready with nil SessionManager\nWHEN handler executes\nTHEN response SHALL be HTTP 503 with JSON {\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-010: Invoke Handler\n\n**GIVEN** invocation requests need to be routed to sandbox  \n**WHEN** handling AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter invocation  \n**THEN** request shall be proxied to the correct sandbox endpoint\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: handleAgentInvoke delegates to handleInvoke\nGIVEN pkg/router/server.go\nWHEN reading handleAgentInvoke method\nTHEN it SHALL call handleInvoke(c, types.AgentRuntimeKind)\n\n// Scenario 2: handleCodeInterpreterInvoke delegates\nGIVEN pkg/router/server.go\nWHEN reading handleCodeInterpreterInvoke method\nTHEN it SHALL call handleInvoke(c, types.CodeInterpreterKind)\n\n// Scenario 3: SessionID from header\nGIVEN invocation request\nWHEN handleInvoke reads sessionID\nTHEN it SHALL read from \"x-agentcube-session-id\" header\n\n// Scenario 4: Parameters extracted from URL\nGIVEN invocation request to /v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-runtime/invocations/api/test\nWHEN handleInvoke processes request\nTHEN namespace SHALL be \"default\"\nAND name SHALL be \"my-runtime\"\nAND invocationPath SHALL be \"/api/test\"\n\n// Scenario 5: GetSandboxBySession called\nGIVEN handleInvoke with valid parameters\nWHEN processing request\nTHEN sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession SHALL be called with ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind\n\n// Scenario 6: No entry point error\nGIVEN sandbox with empty EntryPoints\nWHEN handleInvoke processes request\nTHEN response SHALL be HTTP 404 with JSON {\"error\": \"no entry point configured\", \"code\": \"NO_ENTRY_POINT\"}\n\n// Scenario 7: UpdateSessionLastActivity before proxy\nGIVEN successful sandbox lookup\nWHEN before proxying request\nTHEN storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity SHALL be called with current time\n\n// Scenario 8: Entry point selection\nGIVEN sandbox with multiple entry points\nWHEN selecting entry point\nTHEN selectEntryPoint SHALL be called with entryPoints and invocationPath\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-011: Entry Point Selection\n\n**GIVEN** sandbox has multiple entry points  \n**WHEN** routing request to entry point  \n**THEN** correct entry point shall be selected based on path prefix\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: selectEntryPoint matching path\nGIVEN entry points [{Path: \"/api\"}, {Path: \"/execute\"}] and invocationPath \"/api/v1/resource\"\nWHEN calling selectEntryPoint\nTHEN it SHALL return entry point with Path \"/api\"\n\n// Scenario 2: selectEntryPoint no matching path returns first\nGIVEN entry points [{Path: \"/api\"}, {Path: \"/execute\"}] and invocationPath \"/other/path\"\nWHEN calling selectEntryPoint\nTHEN it SHALL return first entry point as default\n\n// Scenario 3: selectEntryPoint empty entry points\nGIVEN empty entry points slice\nWHEN calling selectEntryPoint\nTHEN it SHALL return nil\n\n// Scenario 4: buildTargetURL with protocol\nGIVEN entry point with Protocol \"http\" and Endpoint \"localhost:8080\"\nWHEN calling buildTargetURL\nTHEN result SHALL be URL with Scheme \"http\" and Host \"localhost:8080\"\n\n// Scenario 5: buildTargetURL with endpoint containing protocol\nGIVEN entry point with empty Protocol and Endpoint \"http://localhost:9000\"\nWHEN calling buildTargetURL\nTHEN result SHALL be URL with Scheme \"http\" and Host \"localhost:9000\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-012: Reverse Proxy\n\n**GIVEN** requests need to be proxied to sandbox  \n**WHEN** implementing reverse proxy  \n**THEN** proper headers and response handling shall be implemented\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: ReverseProxyWrapper struct\nGIVEN pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go\nWHEN reading ReverseProxyWrapper struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain director, modifyResponse, errorHandler function fields\n\n// Scenario 2: Director sets target URL\nGIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper Director function\nWHEN modifying request\nTHEN req.URL.Scheme SHALL be set to target.Scheme\nAND req.URL.Host SHALL be set to target.Host\nAND req.URL.Path SHALL be set correctly\n\n// Scenario 3: Director sets forwarded headers\nGIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper Director function\nWHEN modifying request\nTHEN X-Forwarded-Host header SHALL be set\nAND X-Forwarded-Proto header SHALL be set\nAND X-Forwarded-For header SHALL be set\n\n// Scenario 4: Director sets JWT Authorization\nGIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper with non-empty jwt parameter\nWHEN modifying request\nTHEN Authorization header SHALL be \"Bearer \" + jwt\n\n// Scenario 5: ModifyResponse sets session header\nGIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper ModifyResponse function\nWHEN modifying response\nTHEN x-agentcube-session-id header SHALL be set\n\n// Scenario 6: ErrorHandler connection refused\nGIVEN error message containing \"connection refused\"\nWHEN ErrorHandler handles error\nTHEN response SHALL be HTTP 502 with JSON {\"error\": \"sandbox unreachable\"}\n\n// Scenario 7: ErrorHandler timeout\nGIVEN error message containing \"timeout\"\nWHEN ErrorHandler handles error\nTHEN response SHALL be HTTP 504 with JSON {\"error\": \"sandbox timeout\"}\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-013: JWT Manager\n\n**GIVEN** Router needs JWT token generation for sandbox authentication  \n**WHEN** implementing JWT management  \n**THEN** JWTManager shall generate RS256 signed tokens\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: JWTManager struct\nGIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\nWHEN reading JWTManager struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey and publicKey *rsa.PublicKey fields\n\n// Scenario 2: NewJWTManager constructor\nGIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\nWHEN calling NewJWTManager()\nTHEN it SHALL generate RSA key with size 2048\nAND it SHALL return *JWTManager with keys initialized\n\n// Scenario 3: GenerateToken method\nGIVEN JWTManager instance\nWHEN calling GenerateToken(claims)\nTHEN token SHALL use jwt.SigningMethodRS256\nAND token SHALL contain exp claim with 5 minute expiration\nAND token SHALL contain iat claim with current time\nAND token SHALL contain iss claim \"agentcube-router\"\nAND custom claims SHALL be added to token\n\n// Scenario 4: JWTSigningError on failure\nGIVEN JWTManager signing failure\nWHEN GenerateToken returns error\nTHEN it SHALL return JWTSigningError wrapping the underlying error\n\n// Scenario 5: RSA constants\nGIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\nWHEN reading constants\nTHEN rsaKeySize SHALL be 2048\nAND jwtExpiration SHALL be 5 minutes\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-014: Identity Namespace\n\n**GIVEN** Router needs configurable namespace  \n**WHEN** setting identity namespace  \n**THEN** it shall read from environment variable\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: IdentityNamespace default\nGIVEN AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE environment variable not set\nWHEN init() function executes\nTHEN IdentityNamespace SHALL be \"default\"\n\n// Scenario 2: IdentityNamespace from environment\nGIVEN AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE environment variable set to \"my-namespace\"\nWHEN init() function executes\nTHEN IdentityNamespace SHALL be \"my-namespace\"\n\n// Scenario 3: IdentitySecretName constant\nGIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\nWHEN reading constants\nTHEN IdentitySecretName SHALL be \"picod-router-identity\"\n\n// Scenario 4: Key data key constants\nGIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\nWHEN reading constants\nTHEN PrivateKeyDataKey SHALL be \"private.pem\"\nAND PublicKeyDataKey SHALL be \"public.pem\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-015: Custom Error Types\n\n**GIVEN** Router needs unified error handling  \n**WHEN** defining error types  \n**THEN** all errors shall implement APIStatus interface\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: APIStatus interface\nGIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\nWHEN reading APIStatus interface\nTHEN it SHALL define Status() int\nAND it SHALL define Code() string\nAND it SHALL define Message() string\n\n// Scenario 2: SessionNotFoundError\nGIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\nWHEN reading SessionNotFoundError struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain SessionID string field\nAND Status() SHALL return 404\nAND Code() SHALL return \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\nAND Message() SHALL return \"session not found\"\n\n// Scenario 3: SandboxUnreachableError\nGIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\nWHEN reading SandboxUnreachableError struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain SandboxID string field\nAND Status() SHALL return 502\nAND Code() SHALL return \"SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE\"\n\n// Scenario 4: SandboxTimeoutError\nGIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\nWHEN reading SandboxTimeoutError struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain SandboxID string field\nAND Status() SHALL return 504\nAND Code() SHALL return \"SANDBOX_TIMEOUT\"\n\n// Scenario 5: JWTSigningError\nGIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\nWHEN reading JWTSigningError struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain Err error field\nAND Status() SHALL return 500\nAND Code() SHALL return \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n\n// Scenario 6: ServerOverloadedError\nGIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\nWHEN reading ServerOverloadedError struct\nTHEN Status() SHALL return 429\nAND Code() SHALL return \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"\n\n// Scenario 7: NoEntryPointError\nGIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\nWHEN reading NoEntryPointError struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain SandboxID string field\nAND Status() SHALL return 404\nAND Code() SHALL return \"NO_ENTRY_POINT\"\n\n// Scenario 8: WorkloadManagerError\nGIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\nWHEN reading WorkloadManagerError struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain StatusCode int and Msg string fields\nAND Code() SHALL return \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_ERROR\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-016: Concurrency Limit Middleware\n\n**GIVEN** Router needs to limit concurrent requests  \n**WHEN** implementing concurrency middleware  \n**THEN** requests exceeding limit shall receive 429 response\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: concurrencyLimitMiddleware function\nGIVEN pkg/router/middleware.go\nWHEN reading concurrencyLimitMiddleware function\nTHEN it SHALL use semaphore channel for concurrency control\n\n// Scenario 2: Request allowed within limit\nGIVEN concurrency limit of 1000\nWHEN request arrives within limit\nTHEN request SHALL proceed via c.Next()\n\n// Scenario 3: Request rejected over limit\nGIVEN concurrency limit exceeded\nWHEN request arrives\nTHEN response SHALL be HTTP 429\nAND JSON body SHALL contain {\"error\": \"server overloaded, please try again later\", \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}\nAND c.Abort() SHALL be called\n\n// Scenario 4: Default limit when config invalid\nGIVEN maxConcurrent <= 0\nWHEN middleware initialized\nTHEN limit SHALL be set to 1000\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-017: Logging Middleware\n\n**GIVEN** requests need structured logging  \n**WHEN** implementing logging middleware  \n**THEN** request details shall be logged\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: loggingMiddleware function\nGIVEN pkg/router/middleware.go\nWHEN reading loggingMiddleware function\nTHEN it SHALL capture request start time\nAND it SHALL call c.Next() and then log\n\n// Scenario 2: Log fields captured\nGIVEN loggingMiddleware processing request\nWHEN request completes\nTHEN logger.Info SHALL be called\nAND log SHALL contain method, path, status, duration fields\n\n// Scenario 3: Nil logger handled\nGIVEN loggingMiddleware with nil logger\nWHEN request completes\nTHEN no logging SHALL occur\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-018: Recovery Middleware\n\n**GIVEN** panics in handlers need recovery  \n**WHEN** implementing recovery middleware  \n**THEN** panics shall be caught and 500 response returned\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: recoveryMiddleware function\nGIVEN pkg/router/middleware.go\nWHEN reading recoveryMiddleware function\nTHEN it SHALL use defer with recover()\n\n// Scenario 2: Panic recovered\nGIVEN handler panics\nWHEN recoveryMiddleware catches panic\nTHEN logger.Error SHALL be called with error, path, method fields\nAND response SHALL be HTTP 500 with JSON {\"error\": \"internal server error\"}\nAND c.Abort() SHALL be called\n\n// Scenario 3: Nil logger handled\nGIVEN recoveryMiddleware with nil logger\nWHEN panic occurs\nTHEN no logging SHALL occur\nAND HTTP 500 response SHALL still be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-019: Server Lifecycle\n\n**GIVEN** Server needs graceful startup and shutdown  \n**WHEN** managing server lifecycle  \n**THEN** Start and Stop methods shall be properly implemented\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Start method without TLS\nGIVEN Server with EnableTLS false\nWHEN calling Start(ctx)\nTHEN httpServer.ListenAndServe SHALL be called\nAND waitForShutdown SHALL be started in goroutine\n\n// Scenario 2: Start method with TLS\nGIVEN Server with EnableTLS true and valid TLSCert/TLSKey\nWHEN calling Start(ctx)\nTHEN httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS SHALL be called\n\n// Scenario 3: TLS config validation\nGIVEN Server with EnableTLS true but missing TLSCert or TLSKey\nWHEN calling Start(ctx)\nTHEN it SHALL return error \"TLS cert and key are required when EnableTLS is true\"\n\n// Scenario 4: waitForShutdown behavior\nGIVEN Server.Start called\nWHEN ctx.Done() channel closes\nTHEN shutdownCtx SHALL be created with 10 second timeout\nAND httpServer.Shutdown SHALL be called\n\n// Scenario 5: Stop method\nGIVEN running Server\nWHEN calling Stop()\nTHEN httpServer.Shutdown SHALL be called with 10 second timeout context\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-020: Logger Interface\n\n**GIVEN** Router needs structured logging  \n**WHEN** defining logger abstraction  \n**THEN** Logger interface shall support Info, Error, Warning methods\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Logger interface definition\nGIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\nWHEN reading Logger interface\nTHEN it SHALL define Info(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\nAND it SHALL define Error(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\nAND it SHALL define Warning(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n\n// Scenario 2: Logger used in Server\nGIVEN Server struct\nWHEN reading the implementation\nTHEN logger field SHALL be of type Logger\n\n// Scenario 3: Logger used in middleware\nGIVEN loggingMiddleware and recoveryMiddleware\nWHEN logging events\nTHEN Logger interface methods SHALL be used\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-021: Error Handling in Server\n\n**GIVEN** Server needs unified error responses  \n**WHEN** handling errors in handlers  \n**THEN** handleGetSandboxError shall map errors to correct HTTP codes\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Kubernetes NotFound error\nGIVEN apierrors.IsNotFound(err) true\nWHEN handleGetSandboxError called\nTHEN response SHALL be HTTP 404\n\n// Scenario 2: APIStatus error\nGIVEN error implementing apierrors.APIStatus\nWHEN handleGetSandboxError called\nTHEN HTTP status code SHALL be extracted from APIStatus\nAND message SHALL be extracted from APIStatus\nAND HTTP 500 message SHALL be \"internal server error\"\n\n// Scenario 3: Router APIStatus error\nGIVEN error implementing router.APIStatus\nWHEN handleGetSandboxError called\nTHEN response SHALL use routerErr.Status() for HTTP code\nAND JSON SHALL contain error, code fields\n\n// Scenario 4: Unknown error\nGIVEN error not implementing APIStatus\nWHEN handleGetSandboxError called\nTHEN response SHALL be HTTP 500 with {\"error\": \"internal server error\"}\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-022: Unit Tests\n\n**GIVEN** implementation needs test coverage  \n**WHEN** verifying functionality  \n**THEN** unit tests shall cover all core components\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: session_manager tests\nGIVEN pkg/router/session_manager_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN NewSessionManager tests SHALL verify WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL requirement\nAND GetSandboxBySession tests SHALL verify existing session lookup\nAND GetSandboxBySession tests SHALL verify session creation\nAND createSandbox tests SHALL verify endpoint selection\nAND tests SHALL verify error handling\n\n// Scenario 2: server tests\nGIVEN pkg/router/server_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN NewServer tests SHALL verify constructor with various configs\nAND health endpoint tests SHALL verify /health/live and /health/ready\nAND route registration tests SHALL verify all routes present\nAND lifecycle tests SHALL verify Start/Stop/GracefulShutdown\nAND TLS tests SHALL verify TLS requirement validation\n\n// Scenario 3: errors tests\nGIVEN pkg/router/errors_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN all error types SHALL have tests verifying Error(), Status(), Code(), Message()\nAND APIStatus interface compliance SHALL be tested\n\n// Scenario 4: reverse_proxy tests\nGIVEN pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN selectEntryPoint tests SHALL verify path matching\nAND buildTargetURL tests SHALL verify URL construction\n\n// Scenario 5: middleware tests\nGIVEN pkg/router/middleware_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN concurrencyLimit tests SHALL verify limit enforcement\nAND logging tests SHALL verify log output\nAND recovery tests SHALL verify panic handling\n\n// Scenario 6: jwt tests\nGIVEN pkg/router/jwt_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN NewJWTManager tests SHALL verify key generation\nAND GenerateToken tests SHALL verify token creation and claims\n\n// Scenario 7: config tests\nGIVEN pkg/router/config_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN DefaultConfig tests SHALL verify default values\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-023: Code Quality\n\n**GIVEN** code needs to meet quality standards  \n**WHEN** running linting and validation  \n**THEN** code shall pass go vet and build\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: go vet passes\nGIVEN pkg/router/\nWHEN running go vet ./pkg/router/...\nTHEN zero issues SHALL be reported\n\n// Scenario 2: Build succeeds\nGIVEN pkg/router/\nWHEN running go build ./pkg/router/...\nTHEN build SHALL succeed without errors\n\n// Scenario 3: Test coverage threshold\nGIVEN pkg/router/\nWHEN running go test -cover ./pkg/router/...\nTHEN coverage SHALL be greater than 80%\n\n// Scenario 4: All tests pass\nGIVEN pkg/router/\nWHEN running go test ./pkg/router/...\nTHEN all tests SHALL pass without failures\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-024: Package Documentation\n\n**GIVEN** package needs documentation  \n**WHEN** organizing package structure  \n**THEN** proper documentation shall be present\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: doc.go file exists\nGIVEN pkg/router/\nWHEN listing files\nTHEN doc.go SHALL exist\n\n// Scenario 2: Interfaces documented\nGIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\nWHEN reading the file\nTHEN Store, Logger, SessionManager, JWTManagerInterface, APIStatus interfaces SHALL be defined\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-025: SandboxInfo Types\n\n**GIVEN** Router uses sandbox info types  \n**WHEN** working with sandbox data  \n**THEN** types shall support all necessary fields\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: SandboxInfo struct\nGIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\nWHEN reading SandboxInfo struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain Kind, SandboxID, SandboxNamespace, SandboxName, Name, SessionID, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status, EntryPoints fields\nAND all fields SHALL have JSON tags\n\n// Scenario 2: SandboxEntryPoint struct\nGIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\nWHEN reading SandboxEntryPoint struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain Path, Protocol, Endpoint fields with JSON tags\n\n// Scenario 3: CreateSandboxRequest struct\nGIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\nWHEN reading CreateSandboxRequest struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain Kind, Name, Namespace fields with JSON tags\nAND Validate method SHALL validate all fields\n\n// Scenario 4: CreateSandboxResponse struct\nGIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\nWHEN reading CreateSandboxResponse struct\nTHEN it SHALL contain SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints fields with JSON tags\n\n// Scenario 5: Kind constants\nGIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\nWHEN reading constants\nTHEN AgentRuntimeKind SHALL be \"AgentRuntime\"\nAND CodeInterpreterKind SHALL be \"CodeInterpreter\"\nAND SandboxKind SHALL be \"Sandbox\"\nAND SandboxClaimKind SHALL be \"SandboxClaim\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager implementation with GetSandboxBySession and createSandbox |\n| `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTPServer implementation with Gin framework, routes, and lifecycle |\n| `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | ReverseProxyWrapper, selectEntryPoint, buildTargetURL |\n| `pkg/router/middleware.go` | concurrencyLimitMiddleware, loggingMiddleware, recoveryMiddleware |\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager with RSA key generation and token signing |\n| `pkg/router/errors.go` | Custom error types implementing APIStatus interface |\n| `pkg/router/config.go` | Config struct and DefaultConfig function |\n| `pkg/router/doc.go` | Interface definitions: Store, Logger, SessionManager, APIStatus |\n| `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | SessionManager unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Server unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Reverse proxy and entry point tests |\n| `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Middleware unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT manager unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Error types unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/config_test.go` | Config unit tests |\n| `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` | SandboxInfo, SandboxEntryPoint, request/response types |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `net/http` | HTTP server and client |\n| `context` | Request context for cancellation |\n| `time` | Time handling for sessions and timeouts |\n| `encoding/json` | JSON marshaling for requests/responses |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP router framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT token generation |\n| `golang.org/x/net/http2` | HTTP2 transport support |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | Kubernetes error types |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `/health/live` | GET | Kubernetes liveness probe |\n| `/health/ready` | GET | Kubernetes readiness probe |\n| `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET, POST | AgentRuntime invocation proxy |\n| `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET, POST | CodeInterpreter invocation proxy |\n\n---\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Session ID not found in store |\n| `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | 404 | No entry point configured for sandbox |\n| `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | 502 | Sandbox endpoint connection refused |\n| `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | 504 | Sandbox endpoint timeout |\n| `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | 500 | JWT token signing failure |\n| `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | 429 | Concurrent request limit exceeded |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_ERROR` | varies | Error from WorkloadManager |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] SessionManager correctly creates and retrieves sessions\n- [ ] GetSandboxBySession handles existing sessions and creates new ones\n- [ ] createSandbox sends correct requests to WorkloadManager\n- [ ] Store interface supports session persistence\n- [ ] Service account token correctly added to requests\n- [ ] Server properly configured with Gin framework\n- [ ] All routes registered with correct middleware\n- [ ] Health endpoints respond correctly\n- [ ] Invoke handlers route requests to sandbox entry points\n- [ ] Entry point selection works correctly\n- [ ] Reverse proxy sets proper headers\n- [ ] JWTManager generates valid RS256 tokens\n- [ ] All error types implement APIStatus interface\n- [ ] Middleware enforces concurrency limit\n- [ ] Logging middleware captures request details\n- [ ] Recovery middleware handles panics\n- [ ] Server lifecycle supports graceful shutdown\n- [ ] Logger interface supports structured logging\n- [ ] Error handling maps to correct HTTP codes\n- [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n- [ ] Build succeeds without errors\n- [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n- [ ] All tests pass without failures"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/openc